"{\"uid\": \"newseu.cgtn.com-news-2024-05-06-Non-Paris-Olympics-organizers-battle-against-widespread-English-usage-1tl2RTuz4Fq-p.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 145, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You can change your cookie settings through your browser.\", \"from\": 146, \"to\": 203, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Matthew Nash  Copied  French organizers want their own language to be at the forefront of the Games.\", \"from\": 205, \"to\": 305, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 205, \"end\": 217, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthew_Nash\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Matthew Nash\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q628099\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthew_Nash\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthew_Nash\"}, {\"begin\": 227, \"end\": 233, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 1.4835583161644814e-12, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"/Benoit Tessier/Reuters  Having long battled the creeping use of English in advertising, music and film, French MPs have declared a new struggle: keeping their home Olympics this year free from anglicisms.\", \"from\": 306, \"to\": 511, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 411, \"end\": 421, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Parliament\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French MPs\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q11204\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Parliament\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Parliament\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a resolution adopted on Thursday, the lower house of parliament urged organizers of the 2024 Paris Games, as well as athletes, trainers and journalists to use French as much as possible.\", \"from\": 513, \"to\": 702, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 675, \"end\": 681, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 1.4835583161644814e-12, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Annie Genevard, the conservative sponsor of the resolution, expressed alarm to fellow MPs that \\\"the Olympic Games reflect the loss of influence of our language.\\\"\", \"from\": 704, \"to\": 865, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 704, \"end\": 718, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Annie_Genevard\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Annie Genevard\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Annie_Genevard\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Annie_Genevard\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She recalled the much-criticised slogan used for Paris' original bid for the Games - \\\"Made for Sharing\\\" - as well as other recent government-backed campaigns to promote the country such as \\\"Choose France\\\" or \\\"Made in France\\\".\", \"from\": 867, \"to\": 1092, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 916, \"end\": 921, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.960231430323758e-21, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1084, \"end\": 1090, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999985188879, \"rank\": 1.4773791744483006e-09, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even the French rugby team had 'Rugby World Cup' inscribed on their jerseys during the competition in France last year instead of 'La Coupe du Monde de rugby'.\", \"from\": 1094, \"to\": 1253, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1103, \"end\": 1120, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French rugby team\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1196, \"end\": 1202, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999985188879, \"rank\": 1.4773791744483006e-09, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"All of these examples demonstrate that the fight for the French language... is never finished, even in the most official spheres,\\\" Genevard added.\", \"from\": 1254, \"to\": 1401, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1312, \"end\": 1327, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.435949551493122e-16, \"text\": \"French language\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The march of English globally has long infuriated French governments who have sought to protect the purity of their language at home while promoting its use abroad.\", \"from\": 1403, \"to\": 1567, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1453, \"end\": 1459, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 1.4835583161644814e-12, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The country has an institution - the Academie Francaise - which has produced state-sanctioned dictionaries for three centuries that document and approve new terms or expressions, often translations of commonly-used English words.\", \"from\": 1569, \"to\": 1798, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1784, \"end\": 1791, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/English_language\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.222943188835044e-16, \"text\": \"English\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/English_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/English_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Let us hope that 'planche a roulettes' replaces skateboard and 'rouleau du cap' point break (a surfing term) but I have my doubts,\\\" added Genevard.\", \"from\": 1800, \"to\": 1948, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris's Hotel de Ville City Hall displays the Olympic rings ahead of the arrival of the Games this summer.\", \"from\": 1950, \"to\": 2056, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1950, \"end\": 1955, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.960231430323758e-21, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1958, \"end\": 1972, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seat_of_government\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.254536656540926e-23, \"text\": \"Hotel de Ville\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seat_of_government\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seat_of_government\"}, {\"begin\": 1973, \"end\": 1982, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City_Hall\", \"score\": 0.9939380704268063, \"rank\": 0.006030469651198593, \"text\": \"City Hall\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City_Hall\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City_Hall\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"/Gonzalo Fuentes/Reuters  Language row  French lawmakers passed landmark legislation 30 years ago designed to protect French, the 1994 Toubon Law, which made the language mandatory for advertising, product-labeling and public announcements.\", \"from\": 2057, \"to\": 2297, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2066, \"end\": 2073, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Fuentes\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0394467102553402e-16, \"text\": \"Fuentes\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Fuentes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Fuentes\"}, {\"begin\": 2074, \"end\": 2081, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.766686358315332e-17, \"text\": \"Reuters\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}, {\"begin\": 2097, \"end\": 2103, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 1.4835583161644814e-12, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 2175, \"end\": 2181, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 1.4835583161644814e-12, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 2192, \"end\": 2202, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toubon_Law\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Toubon Law\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toubon_Law\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toubon_Law\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It also stipulated that radio stations had to play a minimum of 40 percent of French-language songs.\", \"from\": 2299, \"to\": 2399, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But the cultural influence of English, increased latterly by American streaming platforms such as Netflix, means French is constantly infiltrated by new terms, including in the sporting realm.\", \"from\": 2400, \"to\": 2592, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2461, \"end\": 2469, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_English\", \"score\": 0.9211963288836185, \"rank\": 0.08554492490854285, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_English\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_English\"}, {\"begin\": 2498, \"end\": 2505, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netflix\", \"score\": 0.9999999999436113, \"rank\": 5.6283704592387397e-11, \"text\": \"Netflix\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netflix\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netflix\"}, {\"begin\": 2513, \"end\": 2519, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 1.4835583161644814e-12, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"You can not overlook the fact that many global sports events that are broadcast globally have chosen to use English for their communication, in their titles, slogans and advertising,\\\" Culture Minister Rachida Dati told parliament.\", \"from\": 2594, \"to\": 2825, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2796, \"end\": 2808, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachida_Dati\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rachida Dati\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachida_Dati\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachida_Dati\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"READ MORE  The most common 'deepfakes' and how to spot them  Mum and son nominated for Golden Chopsticks award  Olympic refugee team will compete in Paris under new emblem  The Olympic Village awaits athletes in Saint-Ouen-sur-Seine near Paris.\", \"from\": 2827, \"to\": 3071, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2921, \"end\": 2931, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chopsticks\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.7903537105576006e-28, \"text\": \"Chopsticks\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chopsticks\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chopsticks\"}, {\"begin\": 2976, \"end\": 2981, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.960231430323758e-21, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 3004, \"end\": 3019, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.53000379267023e-21, \"text\": \"Olympic Village\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\"}, {\"begin\": 3039, \"end\": 3059, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint-Ouen-sur-Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Saint-Ouen-sur-Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint-Ouen-sur-Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint-Ouen-sur-Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 3065, \"end\": 3070, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.960231430323758e-21, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"/Benoit Tessier/Reuters  Thursday's resolution - backed by the ruling centrists and right-wingers but opposed by the left - was non-binding, she stressed.\", \"from\": 3072, \"to\": 3226, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Instructions for foreign visitors during the Olympics from July 26-August 11 and Paralympics from August 28-September 8 would be provided in English as well as other languages, she added.\", \"from\": 3227, \"to\": 3414, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paris Games have already been embroiled in a row about language after rumours that Franco-Malian R&B star Aya Nakamura was set to sing during the opening ceremony on July 26.\", \"from\": 3416, \"to\": 3594, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3517, \"end\": 3520, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rhythm_and_blues\", \"score\": 0.9999793751256778, \"rank\": 1.765477571640999e-05, \"text\": \"R&B\", \"types\": [\"Q188451\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rhythm_and_blues\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rhythm_and_blues\"}, {\"begin\": 3526, \"end\": 3538, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aya_Nakamura\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Aya Nakamura\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aya_Nakamura\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aya_Nakamura\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The mega-star, the most streamed French artist in the world, mixes French, Arabic and words from West African dialects in her songs such as 'Djadja'.\", \"from\": 3595, \"to\": 3744, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3628, \"end\": 3634, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 1.4835583161644814e-12, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 3736, \"end\": 3742, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Djadja_(song)\", \"score\": 0.5934202699024623, \"rank\": 0.5000000000001412, \"text\": \"Djadja\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q2188189\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Djadja_(song)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Djadja_(song)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She was accused of \\\"vulgarity\\\" and mangling the French language by far-right leader Marine Le Pen in a series of highly personal attacks that were denounced as racist by Dati at the time.\", \"from\": 3746, \"to\": 3933, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3794, \"end\": 3809, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.435949551493122e-16, \"text\": \"French language\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 3830, \"end\": 3843, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marine_Le_Pen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Marine Le Pen\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marine_Le_Pen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marine_Le_Pen\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"France is not and will never be 'Djadja',\\\" far-right MP Julien Odoul said on Thursday.\", \"from\": 3934, \"to\": 4021, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3935, \"end\": 3941, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999985188879, \"rank\": 1.4773791744483006e-09, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 3968, \"end\": 3974, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Djadja_(song)\", \"score\": 0.5934202699024623, \"rank\": 0.5000000000001412, \"text\": \"Djadja\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q2188189\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Djadja_(song)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Djadja_(song)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Historic dominance  The dominance of English at the Olympics is particularly galling from a French perspective given that the modern Games were the invention of a French aristocrat, Pierre de Coubertin, in the late 19th century.\", \"from\": 4023, \"to\": 4251, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4115, \"end\": 4121, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 1.4835583161644814e-12, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 4186, \"end\": 4192, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 1.4835583161644814e-12, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 4205, \"end\": 4224, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pierre_de_Coubertin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pierre de Coubertin\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pierre_de_Coubertin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pierre_de_Coubertin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"French was the lingua franca of the first editions and remains one of the official languages of de Coubertin's successors at the International Olympic Committee, which is headed by former German fencer Thomas Bach.\", \"from\": 4253, \"to\": 4467, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4253, \"end\": 4259, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 1.4835583161644814e-12, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 4382, \"end\": 4413, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 4441, \"end\": 4447, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\", \"score\": 0.9999999127958328, \"rank\": 8.70940738802732e-08, \"text\": \"German\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\"}, {\"begin\": 4455, \"end\": 4466, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Thomas Bach\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bach's French is passable but he prefers to speak to foreign journalists in English.\", \"from\": 4468, \"to\": 4552, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4468, \"end\": 4472, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 2.901938942318452e-13, \"text\": \"Bach\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\"}, {\"begin\": 4475, \"end\": 4481, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 1.4835583161644814e-12, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The resolution by French MPs might also resonate at the headquarters of the Paris 2024 organising committee where many officials, including chief executive Tony Estanguet, regularly pepper their French with anglicisms.\", \"from\": 4554, \"to\": 4772, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4572, \"end\": 4582, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Parliament\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French MPs\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q11204\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Parliament\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Parliament\"